defaultSince 1980 there have been nine fatal accidents involving helicopters operati
defaultng in the offshore oil and gas industry, claiming the lives of 114 offshore workers and helicopter crew. There were 44 reportable non-fatal helicopter incidents in the offshore sector over this period.
default&#xa0;
default1.3
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIt is 25 years since the Piper Alpha disaster in the 
defaultNorth Sea and 23 years since the publication of the Cullen Report which was a watershed moment for operational 
defaultsafety
default in the offshore oil and gas industry. 
defaultKey amongst Cullen’s 106
default recommendations (all of which were accepted by the Government of the day an
defaultd industry) 
defaultwas to institute a safety culture of ‘continuous improvement’ in the offshore industry. 
defaultWe believe that this culture of continuous improvement is critical to improving the safety record of offshore helicopter operations. 
default&#xa0;
default1.4
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe cost of such an 
defaultinquiry would not be prohibitive, given the scale of the industry’s annual contribution to
default national tax revenue (
default£10.6 billion in 2011-12
default). 
defaultFor example,
default the House of Commons Library recently estimated that the 
defaultfull 
defaultcost of the Cullen Inquiry in today’s pr
defaultices would be £5.7m
default. 
